The paper discusses the evaluation and testing of Automated Vehicles (AVs), which falls under the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The proposed method involves using statistical models and Importance Sampling theory, which are commonly used in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of simulation results, which can be analyzed using Computer Vision (cs.CV) techniques. Finally, the evaluation of AV safety involves control systems and decision-making algorithms, which are relevant to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
